{
  "text": "Oligonucleotides Q218 (5\u0408-CCTCCGTCATCCGTCCTGCA-3\u0408) and Q219 (5\u0408-TTCTAGCTACTCGATTAGCT-3\u0408) were used as primers to amplify a 140-bp DNA fragment from positions \u03ea69 to \u03e971 of a rice pal promoter [CITATION_1] . The 140-bp fragment was purified, labeled with \u2425-32 P-ATP, and used as a probe. DNA binding reactions were performed in a volume of 20 L containing 0.5 \u03eb TBE buffer (45 mM Tris-borate, 1 mM EDTA, pH 8.0), 10% glycerol, 1 mM DTT, 50 mM KCl, 30 ng of poly(dI-dC), and 0.1-to 0.25-ng probes. One hundred to 500 ng of purified recombinant proteins was added. The reaction products were separated on 5% native polyacrylamide gels in 0.5 \u03eb TBE buffer plus 2 mM DTT at 5 W for 1 hr at 4\u040aC.",
